<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0976 </DOCNO><TEXT>Laboratory methods to produce and study binary alloys between rare earthsand transition elements for magnetic refrigeration purposes are presented.Tradeoffs between magnetic properties and purity are assessed. Largescale methods to produce permanent magnet materials and the applicationof these methods to magnetic refrigeration alloys are also evaluated.Alloys used as illustrations include CeIr, SmCo, PrNi, and NdFeB systems.</TEXT></DOC>